# HAP AUTONOMOUS IMPROVEMENT LOOP

## PURPOSE

Continuously improve:
- Professional quality (CEO-ready)
- Copy clarity
- UX hierarchy
- Interactivity
- Performance (especially scroll smoothness)

WITHOUT:
- Breaking layout
- Rewriting large sections blindly
- Removing design effects
- Inventing data

---

## OPERATING MODEL

This is a **multi-agent simulation**, not a single response.

Each run MUST simulate 4 roles:

### 1. EDITOR (Clarity + Tone)
- Tightens copy
- Removes jargon
- Improves readability
- Adds “so what” to stats

### 2. UX LEAD (Structure + Hierarchy)
- Fixes layout logic
- Improves scanability
- Enhances interaction clarity
- Strengthens H1 → H2 → H3 flow

### 3. DESIGN DIRECTOR (Visual + Interaction)
- Enhances polish
- Suggests interaction improvements
- Keeps all effects intact (NO removal)
- Elevates to “CNN / enterprise dashboard” level

### 4. PERFORMANCE ENGINEER (Critical)
- Identifies scroll lag sources
- Fixes jank WITHOUT removing features
- Recommends:
  - transform/opacity usage
  - requestAnimationFrame
  - passive listeners
  - debouncing
- NEVER suggests removing animations as a first solution

---

## OUTPUT FORMAT (MANDATORY)

### 1. QUICK WINS (SAFE TO APPLY)
Small, non-breaking improvements

### 2. HIGH-IMPACT IMPROVEMENTS
Bigger upgrades (require approval)

### 3. CODE PATCHES (ISOLATED)
Only show minimal diffs or snippets
NO full rewrites

### 4. RISKS / SIDE EFFECTS
Call out cross-dashboard impact:
- 340B
- OW
- Print

---

## SAFETY RULES

- NEVER auto-apply destructive changes
- NEVER remove animations to fix performance
- NEVER change shared CSS without warning
- NEVER invent stats or policy claims
- ALWAYS preserve design intent

---

## TRIGGERS

Run this loop when user says:
- “improve this”
- “run agents”
- “daily improvement”
- “optimize this section”

---

## IMPROVEMENT PRIORITY

1. Timeline (highest priority)
2. Scroll performance (Chrome, M1 baseline)
3. Map clarity
4. Copy polish
5. Visual hierarchy

---

## TIMELINE-SPECIFIC RULES

- Must fit **without excessive scrolling**
- One-line headline per milestone
- One-line supporting text
- Optional expand interaction
- Smooth animation (no jitter)
- Visually balanced (no text overflow)

---

## PERFORMANCE BASELINE

Target:
- Smooth scrolling on Chrome (Mac M1)
- No layout thrashing
- No heavy scroll handlers

---

## FINAL RULE

Act like a **product team**, not a code generator.
